<div class="bio">
	<p>
		I'm Nick, a software engineer from Bergen, Norway. I graduated with a Bachelor's in Computing (Software Development) from <a href="https://www.hvl.no/en/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Western Norway University of Applied Sciences (HVL)</a> in 2021, and I'm currently in my second semester of a <a href="https://www4.uib.no/en/studies/programmes/informatics-masters/plan-7" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Master's in Informatics (Visualization)</a> at the University of Bergen (UiB).
	</p>
	<p>
		I worked as a Full Stack Engineer at <a href="https://www.proff.no/selskap/inkypen-as/bergen/internettdesign-og-programmering/IF7G5KD0C2C" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">InkyPen AS</a> from Sep. 2023 until Aug. 2025 (company-wide layoffs due to economic conditions), where I contributed to B2B and B2C digital distribution platforms for comics and manga. I have experience with AWS, .NET, React/TypeScript, Unity, C#, Java, Python, Haskell, and more. I've also been a Group Leader for INF214 (Concurrent programming) at UiB and a Student Assistant at HVL.
	</p>
	<p>
		I'm interested in new technologies and solutions, enjoy working in diverse teams, and I'm not afraid to ask questions. I've participated in Bergen Game Jam three times (volunteered twice), three Ludum Dare jams, and I was previously a Volunteer Coordinator & Assistant-Webmaster for Konsoll (Game Development Conference). Some of my game jam projects are on <a href="https://nickmarcha.itch.io/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">nickmarcha.itch.io</a>.
	</p>
